Simple web stack

Image Link: https://imgur.com/AOOjqZF

- What is a server
A server is a powerful and reliable computer
that serves or provides services and resources
to other computers or devices over a network.

- What is the role of the domain name
The domain name is a human-readable representation
of where to get a resource on a network as opposed to IP Address.

- What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
The DNS record www in www.foobar.com is a CNAME Record

- What is the role of the web server
The web server provides the user with static website content

- What is the role of the application server
The application server handles dynamic content and
execute server-side code.

- What is the role of the database
A role database is efficiently and securely store, manage, and retrieve data.

- What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website?
The communication between the server and the computer is done via HTTP.

- SPOF
This infrastructure is a Single Point Of Failure because
there is no backup server is case the active server is down or needs maintenance.

- Downtime when maintenance needed (like deploying new code web server needs to be restarted)
Because there is no backup server, no user can access the content on the server.

- Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic
This infrastructure can not scale if theres too much incoming traffic.
